---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — missionctl"
  description="Privacy policy for missionctl.sh. Controller: Gerwin Weiher. GDPR-compliant. Last updated July 2026."
>
  <article style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 5rem 1.5rem;">
    <header style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
      <div style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: #00d97e; margin-bottom: 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase;">Legal</div>
      <h1 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 900; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p style="color: #4a5568; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8rem;">Last updated: 4 July 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div style="color: #a0aec0; line-height: 1.75; font-size: 0.95rem;">

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">1. Controller</h2>
        <p>The controller responsible for processing your personal data in connection with this website is:</p>
        <div style="background: #111118; border: 1px solid #1e1e2e; border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.25rem; margin: 1rem 0; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #e2e8f0;">
          Gerwin Weiher<br>
          E-mail: <a href="mailto:contact@missionctl.sh" style="color: #00d97e; text-decoration: none;">contact@missionctl.sh</a><br>
          Website: <a href="https://missionctl.sh" style="color: #00d97e; text-decoration: none;">https://missionctl.sh</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">2. What data we collect</h2>

        <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;">2.1 The missionctl tools (desktop apps)</h3>
        <p>The missionctl CLI/TUI tools run entirely on your local machine. <strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">No data from your email, calendar, tasks, notes, budget, or social accounts is ever transmitted to our servers.</strong> All data is stored locally in SQLite databases on your computer. We have no access to it.</p>

        <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;">2.2 This website (missionctl.sh)</h3>
        <p>When you visit this website, our hosting provider may log standard server access logs including:</p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0.75rem 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem;">
          <li>IP address (anonymized where possible)</li>
          <li>Browser type and version</li>
          <li>Pages visited and timestamp</li>
          <li>Referring URL</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These logs are retained for a maximum of 30 days and used solely to diagnose technical issues. We do not use third-party analytics or tracking pixels.</p>

        <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;">2.3 Purchase data (polar.sh)</h3>
        <p>Purchases are processed by <a href="https://polar.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: #00d97e; text-decoration: none;">polar.sh</a>, an independent payment processor. When you purchase a missionctl product, polar.sh collects and processes your payment information (name, email, payment details) under their own <a href="https://polar.sh/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: #00d97e; text-decoration: none;">Privacy Policy</a>. We receive only a notification of the purchase (product, amount, and your email address) to fulfill your order.</p>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">3. Legal basis for processing</h2>
        <p>We process personal data only where we have a legal basis:</p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0.75rem 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem;">
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Contractual necessity (Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR)</strong> — order fulfillment after purchase</li>
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR)</strong> — server access logs for security and uptime</li>
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR)</strong> — any future optional analytics, if you opt in</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">4. Cookies</h2>
        <p>This website uses only a single essential cookie to remember your cookie notice acknowledgement. We do not currently use analytics or tracking cookies. See our <a href="/cookies" style="color: #00d97e; text-decoration: none;">Cookie Policy</a> for details.</p>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">5. Data retention</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0.75rem 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem;">
          <li>Server access logs: 30 days</li>
          <li>Purchase records (via polar.sh): per polar.sh retention policy</li>
          <li>Order confirmation emails: until you request deletion</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">6. Third-party processors</h2>
        <div style="border: 1px solid #1e1e2e; border-radius: 6px; overflow: hidden; margin-top: 1rem;">
          <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.875rem;">
            <thead>
              <tr style="background: #0a0a0f; border-bottom: 1px solid #1e1e2e;">
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: #4a5568; font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">Processor</th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: #4a5568; font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">Purpose</th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: #4a5568; font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">Privacy Policy</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #1e1e2e;">
                <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: #e2e8f0; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8rem;">polar.sh</td>
                <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: #718096;">Payment processing &amp; product delivery</td>
                <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem;"><a href="https://polar.sh/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: #00d97e; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.8rem;">polar.sh/legal/privacy</a></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">7. Your rights (GDPR Art. 15–21)</h2>
        <p>Under the GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0.75rem 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem;">
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Art. 15 — Right of access:</strong> Request a copy of personal data we hold about you.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Art. 16 — Right to rectification:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Art. 17 — Right to erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Art. 18 — Right to restriction:</strong> Request that we restrict processing of your data.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Art. 20 — Right to portability:</strong> Receive your data in a machine-readable format.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: #e2e8f0;">Art. 21 — Right to object:</strong> Object to processing based on legitimate interest.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@missionctl.sh" style="color: #00d97e; text-decoration: none;">contact@missionctl.sh</a>. We will respond within 30 days. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your national supervisory authority.</p>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">8. International transfers</h2>
        <p>We do not transfer personal data outside the EEA, except where polar.sh processes payment data. polar.sh's transfers are governed by their data processing agreement and applicable safeguards.</p>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">9. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this policy as our services change. The date at the top of this page indicates the last revision. Continued use of missionctl.sh after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0 0 1rem;">10. Contact</h2>
        <p>For any privacy-related questions or data requests:</p>
        <p>Email: <a href="mailto:contact@missionctl.sh" style="color: #00d97e; text-decoration: none;">contact@missionctl.sh</a></p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
